1
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:17,400
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,680
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,160 --> 00:00:40,080
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,520
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 5]

23
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:43,540
Those bastards actually went for it!

24
00:01:44,350 --> 00:01:46,460
They're running
a kill-or-be-killed operation.

25
00:01:46,870 --> 00:01:48,290
I keep thinking about that doll.

26
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:51,290
That photo of my mentor
with the red X on it

27
00:01:51,310 --> 00:01:52,410
was already a warning.

28
00:01:52,430 --> 00:01:53,770
Then why send another one?

29
00:01:53,790 --> 00:01:54,820
It's an escalation!

30
00:01:54,870 --> 00:01:56,180
This time,
they actually made a move on him!

31
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:58,130
Say they've been playing games with us

32
00:01:58,150 --> 00:01:58,930
and losing every time.

33
00:01:58,950 --> 00:02:01,020
So they get pissed and try to retaliate.

34
00:02:01,790 --> 00:02:03,850
They planted that doll
in my mentor's car.

35
00:02:03,870 --> 00:02:05,260
That means they had the ability

36
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:07,210
to take things further and hurt him.

37
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:09,060
But they didn't.

38
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:09,980
Why?

39
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,610
So it's not retaliation.

40
00:02:14,030 --> 00:02:15,820
It's a heads-up for what's coming next.

41
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:18,570
But the doll itself carries no message.

42
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:21,850
No message might be the message.

43
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:24,780
Shihuo, what is that, a riddle?

44
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,820
You can't catch me.

45
00:02:33,870 --> 00:02:35,610
You can't catch me.

46
00:02:37,030 --> 00:02:37,890
The doll…

47
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:40,610
the doll itself is the message.

48
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,060
Hello, this way please.

49
00:02:59,430 --> 00:03:00,890
This way.

50
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:01,780
Hello, this way.

51
00:03:08,870 --> 00:03:10,610
What if we got it wrong?

52
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:11,610
It's been days.

53
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:13,170
Not a single suspicious doll so far.

54
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,220
What's the rush?

55
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:17,450
As long as
we don't let any smugglers slip through,

56
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,690
we're good.

57
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:20,690
Keep it moving back there.

58
00:03:20,870 --> 00:03:22,540
[Shenmu Travel Group]
Over here.

59
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,170
Tour group, gather over here, please.

60
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,340
Come on, let's go.

61
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,820
Is everyone here?

62
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:30,780
Zhang.

63
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,340
Clear the crowd.

64
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:34,890
Today wraps up our trip.

65
00:03:34,910 --> 00:03:37,500
Thanks for sticking with me, everyone.

66
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,570
Yanzi, what's wrong?

67
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:45,730
What happened? You look awful!

68
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:47,660
Get a doctor, now!

69
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:50,010
She's fine, just an upset stomach.

70
00:03:50,310 --> 00:03:51,450
We'll grab some meds once we're out,

71
00:03:51,470 --> 00:03:52,380
she'll be fine.

72
00:03:52,630 --> 00:03:53,690
Then let's get through customs!

73
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:54,410
Yeah.

74
00:03:54,430 --> 00:03:55,290
Take her to a hospital if needed.

75
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:56,570
- Okay. - Just make sure she's alright.

76
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,690
Don't worry, we know what we're doing.

77
00:03:58,710 --> 00:04:00,130
We won't cause any trouble.

78
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:01,570
Alright.

79
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:02,690
Go on, then.

80
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:17,020
Excuse me.

81
00:04:17,830 --> 00:04:19,250
China Customs.
Please cooperate with the inspection.

82
00:04:19,830 --> 00:04:21,490
Inspect what?

83
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:22,490
Your luggage.

84
00:04:22,510 --> 00:04:24,250
Can't you see my daughter's in pain?

85
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:25,700
You're wasting my time!

86
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:26,490
Sir, you can't leave.

87
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:27,980
Sir, you need to stay here.

88
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,140
If something happens,

89
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,700
will you take responsibility?

90
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,850
Look at her, she's in pain.

91
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,660
Our medical room is right here.

92
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,340
Let the doctor check her first,

93
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:36,660
then we'll send her to a hospital.

94
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:38,490
An on-site doctor?

95
00:04:38,510 --> 00:04:40,140
How can we trust that?

96
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:41,850
- Exactly! - She needs a real hospital!

97
00:04:41,870 --> 00:04:42,930
We're leaving now.

98
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:43,540
Listen…

99
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,050
She can't take it anymore!

100
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,610
Let me take a look.

101
00:04:46,630 --> 00:04:48,540
It's nothing, just an upset stomach.

102
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,490
She's fine.

103
00:04:50,070 --> 00:04:51,780
That looks painful!
Here, have some water.

104
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,580
No!

105
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,020
She… she can't drink water.

106
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:56,250
Water makes it worse.

107
00:04:56,270 --> 00:04:57,780
She really can't.

108
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,220
Is that so?

109
00:05:01,190 --> 00:05:02,170
That's the problem.

110
00:05:02,190 --> 00:05:03,780
Your child is unwell.

111
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,980
Come to the medical screening room.
We'll do a checkup.

112
00:05:06,510 --> 00:05:07,610
Hongxia, get over here.

113
00:05:07,630 --> 00:05:09,930
It's just an upset stomach.

114
00:05:10,270 --> 00:05:11,170
Phones.

115
00:05:11,190 --> 00:05:11,980
Put the phones away.

116
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:12,700
Take the child…

117
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,290
take her for an exam.

118
00:05:14,310 --> 00:05:15,020
Where are you taking my child?

119
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:17,100
Stay calm, please cooperate!

120
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,580
Please cooperate. Thank you.

121
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:19,460
You three also

122
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:21,540
need a physical exam.

123
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,660
Fine,

124
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:24,290
but give me my child back!

125
00:05:24,310 --> 00:05:25,370
Don't worry.

126
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:26,050
- You… - Over here.

127
00:05:26,070 --> 00:05:27,250
Take him for a body check.

128
00:05:27,270 --> 00:05:28,850
Give me my child back!

129
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:29,780
Please cooperate.

130
00:05:30,070 --> 00:05:30,850
This way.

131
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,780
Over here, this way.

132
00:05:36,950 --> 00:05:38,980
This could've been handled
with a little flexibility.

133
00:05:39,070 --> 00:05:40,050
Why make a scene?

134
00:05:43,190 --> 00:05:43,730
Tell me,

135
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:46,290
what would your mentor
have done in that situation?

136
00:05:48,270 --> 00:05:49,610
Probably the same as you.

137
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:51,290
Him?

138
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:54,050
He'd have grabbed the kid and moved.

139
00:05:54,070 --> 00:05:55,900
He wouldn't waste time

140
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:56,810
arguing with the father.

141
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:01,440
[Special Examination Room 1]

142
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:07,610
Sit down.

143
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:08,490
Sit.

144
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,290
Sit down!

145
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,810
Officer,

146
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,100
how's Yanzi?

147
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,290
You've got the nerve to ask?

148
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:20,540
You know exactly
what you made her swallow.

149
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,610
This could kill her! Do you understand?

150
00:06:24,630 --> 00:06:25,700
The kid's fine now.

151
00:06:26,630 --> 00:06:28,100
All the capsules have passed.

152
00:06:28,190 --> 00:06:29,540
I'm going to prison…

153
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:31,490
I'm going to prison…

154
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:36,340
I'm not fit to be a mother.

155
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:38,100
I'm a monster!

156
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:40,610
This is all my fault!

157
00:06:41,830 --> 00:06:43,780
I don't deserve to be her mother.

158
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:44,370
Sit down.

159
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,020
The dealer who got me into this…

160
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:50,900
told me…

161
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:54,170
if she swallowed them

162
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:55,220
and didn't eat or drink for four days,

163
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:57,930
she'd be fine.

164
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,660
We just left the hotel…

165
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:00,540
right after she took them…

166
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:02,490
not even a day…

167
00:07:02,510 --> 00:07:03,780
so I thought maybe…

168
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:04,900
Thought what?

169
00:07:05,190 --> 00:07:06,610
Is that even your child?

170
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,290
Why didn't you take them yourself?

171
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:12,490
The dealer said
kids get through customs easier.

172
00:07:12,510 --> 00:07:13,780
Kids don't get checked.

173
00:07:13,870 --> 00:07:14,850
So we…

174
00:07:17,630 --> 00:07:19,490
Bastard!

175
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:20,980
This is all your fault!

176
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:22,660
All your fault!

177
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,220
This family is finished.

178
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:27,810
They may never see their kids again.

179
00:07:28,430 --> 00:07:29,850
They brought this on themselves.

180
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:31,660
I feel sorry for the kids.

181
00:07:32,630 --> 00:07:35,220
This is all on the people behind it.

182
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:37,490
That's what the doll was telling us.

183
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:40,460
Group E is using kids to smuggle drugs.

184
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,610
They went through all that trouble.

185
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,170
No way it's just one shipment.

186
00:07:45,430 --> 00:07:47,370
There have to be more cases like this.

187
00:07:47,390 --> 00:07:47,850
So,

188
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:49,410
I'll report this up the chain,

189
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:51,460
and notify land borders
and cruise terminals

190
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,460
to tighten inspections,

191
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:53,370
okay?

192
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:54,540
Yes, sir.

193
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:01,640
[Train to Satellite Hall]

194
00:08:04,870 --> 00:08:06,250
Hello, this way, please.

195
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,340
Hello.

196
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,930
China Customs.
Please cooperate with the inspection.

197
00:08:17,950 --> 00:08:18,700
Is there a problem?

198
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:20,140
May I see your passport?

199
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:23,780
Here.

200
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:24,900
Thank you.

201
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,340
Coming back from Argentina?

202
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,580
Yeah. Is there a problem?

203
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:34,370
No problem.

204
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:39,010
Cute kid.

205
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,770
Hey there, buddy.

206
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:49,890
Come on.

207
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,580
Let me hold you for a sec, okay?

208
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:52,180
No!

209
00:08:52,390 --> 00:08:53,890
No! Mommy!

210
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:56,890
Something's off.

211
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,220
My child!

212
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,770
Ma'am, please calm down.

213
00:08:59,790 --> 00:09:00,850
Relax, nothing will happen

214
00:09:00,870 --> 00:09:01,530
if that's your child.

215
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:02,460
- They're taking my child! - Mommy!

216
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,420
Calm down.

217
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:04,850
Mommy!

218
00:09:04,870 --> 00:09:05,890
My child!

219
00:09:05,910 --> 00:09:06,820
- Mommy! - Calm down, please.

220
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,220
Put the phones away.

221
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,580
No filming.

222
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,250
Good call moving fast.

223
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,340
The kid's safe.

224
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:17,420
What are you thinking?

225
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:19,300
I remember

226
00:09:19,670 --> 00:09:21,220
that middle-aged woman's suitcase

227
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:23,250
had a Shenmu Travel tag.

228
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:24,940
And the girl from the last case

229
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:26,460
was with Shenmu too.

230
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:27,820
You sure?

231
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:28,530
Positive.

232
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:57,120
[CHINA CUSTOMS]

233
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:59,920
[CHINA CUSTOMS]

234
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:03,420
You okay? Look at you.

235
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:04,220
I'm fine.

236
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:05,770
Is it straight?

237
00:10:06,030 --> 00:10:07,100
Yes.

238
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:10,250
Come in.

239
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:18,030
[Huayan Airport Customs, Binhai]

240
00:10:18,030 --> 00:10:18,770
[Huayan Airport Customs, Binhai]
Everyone,

241
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:21,010
[Huayan Airport Customs, Binhai]
I'm just back from medical leave.

242
00:10:21,030 --> 00:10:22,340
[Huayan Airport Customs, Binhai]
I don't deserve the applause.

243
00:10:22,390 --> 00:10:23,770
But I hear my trainee

244
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:24,850
has been doing a solid job.

245
00:10:24,870 --> 00:10:25,850
While I was gone,

246
00:10:27,030 --> 00:10:27,820
he held things down, huh?

247
00:10:28,150 --> 00:10:29,340
Let's give it up for him.

248
00:10:29,510 --> 00:10:30,340
Chen,

249
00:10:30,510 --> 00:10:31,580
you've got that wrong.

250
00:10:31,790 --> 00:10:32,770
That applause

251
00:10:32,910 --> 00:10:34,460
was for Guo Cong.

252
00:10:36,390 --> 00:10:37,300
Well, that's awkward.

253
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:38,250
Everyone, sit.

254
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:41,100
Alright.

255
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:43,060
Now that we're all here,

256
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:43,940
let's get started.

257
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,130
We have two items

258
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,580
on today's agenda.

259
00:10:47,910 --> 00:10:48,580
First,

260
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,850
the driver who hit Chen

261
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,130
has been arrested.

262
00:10:52,910 --> 00:10:55,250
He's an independent truck driver.

263
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:58,180
He's in custody for DUI

264
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:00,180
and hit-and-run.

265
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:01,700
When he was picked up,

266
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,130
the truck was still in the shop.

267
00:11:03,670 --> 00:11:05,300
Dashcam shows

268
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:07,850
that after hitting Chen's car,

269
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:09,250
he didn't stop.

270
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:10,650
He kept going.

271
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:13,730
He went on to scrape a few more cars

272
00:11:13,910 --> 00:11:15,010
along the way.

273
00:11:16,630 --> 00:11:19,850
But during the investigation,

274
00:11:20,270 --> 00:11:21,530
police found no evidence

275
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:22,940
linking him

276
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,460
to the smuggling ring.

277
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:28,420
He didn't plant the doll?

278
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:29,130
No.

279
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:31,490
That means

280
00:11:31,870 --> 00:11:33,370
there was a third person at the scene.

281
00:11:46,790 --> 00:11:48,060
And that third person

282
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:50,850
is the one we've been looking for

283
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:52,730
this whole time.

284
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:54,820
So, Chen,

285
00:11:55,670 --> 00:11:58,010
stay on guard.

286
00:11:59,270 --> 00:12:00,220
Chief, don't worry.

287
00:12:00,390 --> 00:12:01,770
If they show up,

288
